<paragraph blockId="76.[151,1437,966,2037]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1974,2000]" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen &amp; Pu" authorityYear="1980" box="[612,761,1975,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Adiscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="76" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="occipitalis">
<emphasis box="[612,761,1975,2001]" italics="true" pageId="76" pageNumber="77">A. occipitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the latter has fine and dense punctures on pronotum, its elytra with epipleura hardly visible in lateral view, and venter is yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
